<section id="Removing_Clusters" remap="TID_15256">
	<title>Removing Clusters</title>
	<para>
		If a cluster has been decommissioned or requires troubleshooting, it might require removal from the VMDB.
	</para>
	<procedure>
		<title>To Remove Clusters</title>
		<step>
			<para>
				Navigate to <menuchoice><guimenu>Infrastructure</guimenu><guisubmenu>Clusters</guisubmenu></menuchoice>.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Check the clusters to remove.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click 
				<inlinemediaobject>
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata fileref="images/1847.png" />
					</imageobject>
				</inlinemediaobject> <guibutton>(Configuration)</guibutton>, and then 
				<inlinemediaobject>
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata fileref="images/2157.png" />
					</imageobject>
				</inlinemediaobject> <guibutton>(Remove Clusters from the VMDB)</guibutton>.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click <guilabel>OK</guilabel>.
			</para>
		</step>
	</procedure>
	<formalpara>
		<title>Result:</title>
		<para>
			The clusters are deleted. Any virtual machines or hosts associated with these clusters remain, but are no longer associated with them.
		</para>
	</formalpara>
</section>